\date{}

\begin{abstract}
Let $(X\, ,x_0)$ be a pointed smooth proper variety defined over an algebraically closed field.
The Albanese morphism for $(X\, ,x_0)$ produces
a homomorphism from the abelianization of the $F$-divided fundamental group
scheme of $X$ to the $F$-divided fundamental group of the Albanese
variety of $X$. We
prove that this homomorphism is surjective with finite kernel. The kernel is also
described.
\end{abstract}

